# Erick Stow
Erick Stow is a Canadian-born artist from Saskatoon, Saskatchewan. He grew up in Lubbock, Texas where he received his Bachelor of Arts degree in mass visual communications from Texas Tech University.

Stow has toured the world with his art and has had residencies in Montreal, Calgary, Austin, and Los Angeles. His works are displayed in galleries, with private collectors, and sold in studios internationally.

Stow is the creator of a form of post-expressionism called “motionism”.  He is an award-winning film-maker, writer, actor, and director appearing in major motion pictures, on-stage, indie projects, and music videos.

# About Nirvan
I am a 24 year old model living in Nigeria. I’m a graduate of Bowen University and a disciple of computer science. I am also a fashion model who choose to express myself through gestures and poses on digital media. 

But all these changed after I was introduced to cryptoart in early 2019. I began creating pieces of visual art and poetry which I sold for Ethereum on platforms like Rarible and Opensea. This earned me the title of the first Cryptomodel in Africa because I believe I was one of the first people to sell my own image as art on the blockchain.

I have sold 3 pieces on Rarible the first titled “The Sojourner” followed by a photographic shot titled “Narcissus” then my collaboration with Dagapita for “Tempest” and finally “Roots”. All of these works have resulted in sales with the exception of “Roots” being my recent release.

I also gather influences from a myriad of sources so I can’t point out one. I just go with whatever makes me happy and contented(even though I never think my work is perfect). But I can call myself an Afro-futuristic artist.

SphericalArt, aka Paul Petersen, studied drawing and painting at UCLA with William Brice, earning a Bachelor of Fine Arts degree. He did post graduate study at the Art Center College of Design. He's had careers as an art director, watercolorist, and medical illustrator. His technical proficiency in computer graphics has put him in a position to explore a new area of abstract geometric image creation he calls "Spherical Art". He began his exploration of this method in 2015.

He  finds art in, and around, 3D geometric spheres and other round objects. They are either part of his compositions, or the building blocks behind them. His art is seldom intentional, and mostly discovered as he explores. It ranges from geometric abstract to landscape, to figurative. Hs recent  "Heads"  series are created inside 3D head models.
